Iâ€™m sharing the instructions to run the BudgetApp program:

Requirements

Python 3.x installed (download from python.org
)

Tkinter (included with Python by default)

Download the Code

Save the program as budget_app.py on your computer.

Run the Program

Using Command Line / Terminal:

Open a terminal and navigate to the folder containing budget_app.py

cd path\to\your\folder


Run the program:

python budget_app.py


Using an IDE:

Open budget_app.py in an IDE like PyCharm, VS Code, or IDLE.

Click Run or press the run shortcut (F5 or Shift+F10).

Using the App

Set Monthly Income: Enter your monthly income and click Set monthly.

Add Expenses: Enter the expense name, amount, and date, then click Add Expense.

Add Reminders: Enter the reminder details and click Add Reminder.

Add Goals: Enter your financial goals and click Add Goal.

Check Balance: Click Calculate Balance to see remaining balance and goal status.

View Entries: Use Show Expenses, Show Reminders, or Show Goals buttons to view details.

Notes

Enter amounts as numbers (decimals allowed).

Dates must be in YYYY-MM-DD format.

Data is not saved after closing the app unless modifications are made to store it.
